While there is no tail call optimization, you can trampoline a recursive function call to eliminate issues with blowing the call stack.<p><pre><code>    function trampoline(fn /*, args */) {
        var result = fn.apply(fn, _.rest(arguments));
        while (typeof result === &#x27;function&#x27;) { 
            result = result();
        }
        return result; 
    }
</code></pre>
I learned this wonderful trick from fogus&#x27; functional javascript, which I cannot recommend enough.
